  <front>
   <head>SONNET [36] XXXVI.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">SHOULD the lone Wand'rer, fainting on his way,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Rest for a moment of the sultry hours,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And tho' his path thro' thorns and roughness lay,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Pluck the wild rose, or wood bine's gadding flow'rs;</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Weaving gay wreaths, beneath some shelt'ring tree,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The sense of sorrow, he awhile may lose;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">So have I sought thy flow'rs, fair Poesy!</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">So charm'd my way, with Friendship and the Muse.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But darker now grows Life's unhappy day,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Dark, with new clouds of evil yet to come,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Her pencil sickening Fancy throws away,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And weary Hope reclines upon the tomb;</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And points my wishes to that tranquil shore,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Where the pale spectre Care, pursues no more.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
